latestIgtvVideos.title: Monologue from La La Land
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My new monologue is “The audition scene”, half-spoken, half-sung monologue originally performed by Emma Stone from the movie La La Land. This song received a nomination for best original song at the 89th academy awards. Emma Stone does more for her character  in those four minutes than Mia in 2hours of the movie. An achievement that eventually won her the Oscar for Best Actress. La La Land movie is for anyone chasing a seemingly impossible dream.
Not many of you would understand this monologue..
You really need to watch the film to understand this scene. 
I chose this  because I found this particular monologue quite challenging. As this involves emoting, narrating while singing. I have never done something like this before. 
I thought to myself that if Meryl Streep can sing in Mama Mia and Emma Stone can sing in La la land, despite being a non-singer, why can’t I.. I mean there’s no harm in trying. 
I still feel that I could have performed better, In a different set up. But for now I’m just happy that I tried :) 
Making monologues keeps me going. It’s a liberating experience for me ♥️

Here's to the ones who dream
Foolish as they may seem
Here's to the hearts that ache
Here's to the mess we make 💙
#DamienChazelle
#lalaland #emmastone #monologue #bliss #actor #artist #keeprehearsing  #keeppracticing #hollywood #dowhatyoulove #followyourdreams #followyourbliss #keepdreaming #keepgoing #dreams

latestIgtvVideos.title: Monologue: Kramer vs Kramer (Meryl Streep)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Take your broken heart and turn  it into art ♥️ @merylstreep 
Hi all! 
This time I have tried recreating one of my favourite actors, Meryl Streep’s scene from Kramer vs Kramer. I am a big fan of her! She’s been inspiring actors and fans all over the World for so many years!! She’s stunned us with every film, every character that she’s played. 
 There are still so many films of her on my movie’s bucket list which I need to watch. 
Out of all the films that I have watched till date, my favourite Meryl Streep character would be Miranda Priestly. 
What’s your favourite Meryl Streep movie? Tell me on the comment section. 
Also, this is my first English monologue. It took me almost 2 days to prepare for this one. Hope you guys enjoy watching my version of this scene... It’s been a while that  I have stayed away from the camera. So, I have decided to make more scenes and monologues from my hometown for the love of my craft.
Thank you for all the love and support ♥️ 
Video credits - @anishism02 😘 #monologue #englishmonologue #actor #learner #workinprogress #merylstreep #kramervskramer #hollywood #gratitude #lovemycraft #india

latestPosts.caption:
Visiting our family school yesterday was an incredible experience. This time, I met the kids not just as the founder of the school but as someone who was once a student from the same town. Someone who, at their age, was just as confused and unsure about the future. I wasn't a bright student in school, but I actively participated in extracurricular activities and dreamed of making it big someday.

I highlighted the significance of extracurricular activities and how vital it is to participate in arts, sports, and poetry. I spoke about the importance of moral values and how they shape our personality for the future. I told them not to limit their minds based on caste or religion; humanity should be the only religion for every student.

I made sure to address the not-so-bright students, encouraging them not to feel demotivated. I quoted Albert Einstein: "Everybody is a genius, but if you judge a fish by its ability to climb a tree, it will live its whole life believing it is stupid." I also emphasized how important it is for them to work hard now and give their best while they're young. 
#hometowndiaries #bermo #phusro #jharkhand

latestPosts.caption:
Grief has a way of changing people. I just realized that I had almost stopped taking photos of myself — selfies, basically. It started to feel strange because when life shows you its hardest sides, things like your body, beauty, and appearances start to feel so superficial.

That said, it’s vital that we continue to take care of ourselves and work to free our minds from grief and negative emotions — for the sake of our mental health and peace.

I still remember how hard it was for me to stop crying after I lost my brother. I was overwhelmed with emotions; it felt as if the pain was unbearable and unstoppable. It wasn’t easy to accept the reality. I cried so much and for so many days that eventually, my eyes would start to hurt from all the crying. That’s when I finally stopped — not because I was ready, but because my body simply couldn’t take it anymore.

Even when it feels like the world has stopped, life gently finds a way to move forward. Healing isn’t forgetting — it’s learning to live with love and loss side by side…
